message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Slovakia in the past 20 years is the country's accession to the European Union (EU) on May 1, 2004. This event marked Slovakia's integration into the European community and brought numerous political, economic, and social changes to the country. It opened up new opportunities for trade, investment, and mobility within the EU, and also led to the adoption of various EU laws and regulations. Slovakia's EU membership has played a crucial role in shaping its development and positioning within the European context.
